description._content: Catalog #: 09_01150 Title: Kathryn Fritz Special Collection Photo San Diego California Date: circa 1927 Additional Information: Ryan Standard aircraft on runway at San Diego Aviation Field. Handwritten inscription ""we're off"", Kathryn Fritz was a young woman residing in San Diego during the 1920s. She was an aviation enthusiast and acquaintance of Charles Lindbergh.
